-- Koor, Discount Investment Drop Following Credit Suisse Slide
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-07-22T14:59:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/koor-discount-investment-drop-following-credit-suisse-decline.html
  Koor Industries Ltd. (KOR) , which owns a
stake in  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) , retreated as shares of the
Swiss bank dropped almost 3 percent on July 20.  Koor declined 6.6 percent to 29.80 shekels, the lowest
since Sept. 12, at the 4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv.  IDB Holding
Corp. (IDBH) , which owns a stake in Koor through  Discount Investment
Corp. (DISI) , dropped 6.8 percent to 15 shekels, the weakest level
since July 16. Discount Investment declined 6.2 percent to 5.072
shekels, the lowest level on record for the shares. The
benchmark TA-25 index lost 0.6 percent.  Credit Suisse  shares  dropped 2.9 percent to 16.83 Swiss
francs ($17.03) in Zurich on July 20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
